==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dilation
<hw>Di*la"tion</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>dilate</ets>, v., cf.
<er>Dilatation</er>, <er>Dilator</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of dilating,
or the state of being dilated; expansion; dilatation.</def> <rj><au>Mrs.
Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At first her eye with slow <qex>dilation</qex> rolled.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A gigantic <qex>dilation</qex> of the hateful figure.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dilative</ent>⟦br⟧
